```c
  if (measConfig->measObjectToRemoveList)
    handle_measobj_remove(rrc, measConfig->measObjectToRemoveList, timers);
```

So the issue is:
1. When `measConfig->measObjectToRemoveList` is processed, it calls `handle_measobj_remove` which calls `handle_meas_reporting_remove` for each measurement ID associated with the measurement object.
2. Later, when `measConfig->measIdToRemoveList` is processed, it calls `handle_measid_remove` which again calls `handle_meas_reporting_remove` for the same measurement IDs.

